column13: The nicest place to dine in El Paso. Husband and I went for anniversary and we had a wonderful experience. We were very fortunate to have excellent food. My only comPlaint was the crab cakes. They were ok. A little fishy tasting. The wine list is extensive. The wait staff were extremely nice and attentive. The speed of service is very good. We were never long between courses. Prices are comparable to any other fine dining establishment.
Not good food, looked like the restaurant was about to close. I felt rushed and ignored.
We live on the west side of El Paso and reserve our tups to DeLaneys for special occasions. We consider it one of the two best restaurants in El Paso.

A nice find in Marfa and overall I thought it was pretty good but it was pretty pricey. The waiter did get my order wrong initially which was annoying but he recovered fairly well. I brought the Salmon dish and was a little disappointed with the VERY over cooked fish. Wine list was good but I think a few more Australian wines would make it even better :-)

column4: 2525 N. Mesa St. El Paso, TX  79902
column13: Overall it was an excellent experience. Great food and excellent service for our large group of 11. It was a great night for my special occasion.

THIS HAS BEEN THE BEST DINNER EXPERIANCE I HAVE HAD IN A VERY LONG TIME!!!My friends and I are always looking for a fabulous place to take our possible funders for our non-profit organization. The FOOD, OMG, THE FOOD!!!! We had three appetizers, 4 entrees and a collection of mixed drinks that did not disappoint!
I think this is one of the finest restaurants in Alpine.
